text: Kateřina Holásková (born 9 March 1991) is a Czech volleyball player, playing as a Middle blocker. She is part of the Czech Republic women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2018 Women's European Volleyball League, and 2019 Women's European Volleyball League, winning a gold medal, 2019 EuroVolley, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Challenger Cup. On club level she played for VK TU Liberec, TJ Sokol Šternberk, SK UP Olomouc, and VC Kanti Schaffhausen. == References == Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
